0 SHOOT THROW STUCK 'STUCK IN'~
Syntax: shoot <direction> <target>
Syntax: throw spear <direction> <target>

	In order to be able to shoot, you should wield bow to your pro-hand
and arrow to the other hand. In order to throw spear, you should wield the
spear to your pro-hand. The direction is the throwing or the shooting
direction. The target (2.cityguard) is counted from the room that you are
in. When a victim is stuck by the spear or arrow, it may be stuck in the
body of the victim. In order to remove th stuck in arrow or spear, one
should just type 'remove arrow' or 'remove spear'. If you don't remove
the stuck in item, it will decrease your hitroll, damroll as well as it
will decrease the hitpoint gain. Of course the stuck arrows and spears
inflict damages initially as well. However the mobiles start tracking
the shooter. You can shoot as far range as you can SCAN.
~

0 CAST~
Syntax: cast <spell> <target>

	Before you can cast a spell, you have to practice it. The more you
practice, the higher chance you have of success when casting.  Casting spells
costs mana. The mana cost decreases as your level increases. Also, some skills
may increase the power of your spell.

	The <target> is optional.  Many spells which need targets will use an
appropriate default target, especially during combat. Some spells targets are
rooms, so you don't need a target at all. In order to see the affections of
rooms type RAFFECT.

	In addition you can cast offensive spells to the other rooms as well.

	cast 'acid blast' n.2.fido

	Means, cast the 'acid blast' spell to the fido, who is in the north
direction and counting this room it is the second fido. You can cast as far
as you can see in the SCAN range. However the mobiles start tracking the
person that attacked itself.

	If the spell name is more than one word, then you must quote the spell
name. Example: cast 'cure critic' frag.  Quoting is optional for single-word
spells. You can abbreviate the spell name.

	When you cast an offensive spell, the victim usually gets a saving
throw. The effect of the spell is reduced or eliminated if the victim makes
the saving throw successfully.

See also the help sections for individual spells.
~

0 EXITS~
