Tells you the visible exits of the room you are in.  Not all exits are visible.
You can use the 'bump' technique to find hidden exits.  (Try to walk in a
certain direction and see what you bump into).
~

0 SCAN~
Syntax: scan <direction>

	Scan enables character to see the people around him. If you don't
give a direction as an argument, all directions will be scanned and the
result will be displayed. If you give an argument, then it will display
the mobiles only in that direction and it will display far in that direction
as well.
~

0 DROP GET GIVE PUT TAKE~
Syntax: drop <object>
Syntax: drop <amount> coins
Syntax: get  <object>
Syntax: get  <object> <container>
Syntax: give <object> <character>
Syntax: give <amount> coins <character>
Syntax: put  <object> <container>

DROP drops an object, or some coins, on the ground, e.g:
	drop sword
	drop 2.sword	(means second)
	drop all.sword
	drop 10 silver
	drop all

GET gets an object, either lying on the ground, or from a container, or even
from a corpse.  TAKE is a synonym for get, e.g:
	get sword
	get 3.bracer	(means third)
	get all.sword
	get 10 gold
	get all
	get all corpse		or 	get all from corpse
	get all.bag corpse	or 	get all.bag from corpse
	get ring pit		or	get ring from pit
	get 2.ring pit		or 	get 2.ring from pit	(means second)

GIVE gives an object, or some coins, to another character, e.g:
	give banner cityguard
	give 2.ring cityguard
	give 10 gold cityguard

PUT puts an object into a container, e.g:
	put banner pit		or	put banner in pit
	put banner sofa		or	put banner on sofa
	put all.ring pit	or	put all.ring on sofa


DROP, GET and PUT understand the object names 'ALL' for all objects and
'ALL.object' for all objects with the same name.
~

